data.description: 5 Bedroom 3 bath home in The Lakes Community.  Renovation include new interior and exterior paint, roof is less than a year old 50 year architectural shingles, new granite counter tops and appliances, new flooring in upstairs bedrooms, hall and master bedroom, Hardwood floors in Great room, and 3 main level bedrooms, tiled floors in the den and kitchen. 2 pantries in the kitchen pull out from under stairs and additional pantry by garage door.  The extensive amount of cabinets and counter tops open to the large eat in kitchen. Great-room with vaulted ceiling and fireplace opens to the kitchen and den.  The opening in the den would fit french door should the owner want to create a more private area.  The master bedroom a tray ceiling hard wood floors and a private bath with two walk in closets and large shower. The two guest bedrooms on the main level are located next the to the 2nd full bath.  Upstairs are two bedrooms with vaulted ceiling and the 3rd full guest bath.  Your back yard is accessed from the double gate at the end of the driveway. Enjoy the lagoon/lake store all your lawn equipment in the shed and use the large outbuilding for any additional storage or convert to the he/she shed.  If all of this isn't enough the location will top it all off. Blocks to the elementary, middle school, restaurants and I 95.  Within minutes to Kings Bay Submarine Base and Historic St Marys. Within 30 minutes to Brunswick, Jacksonville and the Florida and Georgia Beaches.  Won't last long!
